# Next.js App Router Conventions

- All web code lives in `web/`. Never place Next.js files at the repo root.
- Use the App Router (`app/` directory). No Pages Router.
- Prefer Server Components by default. Add `"use client"` only when client interactivity is required.
- Co-locate styles with components. Use CSS Modules or Tailwind utility classes.
- API routes go in `web/app/api/`. Server Actions live next to the form or page that uses them.
- Shared types go in `web/lib/types.ts`.
- Data adapters that read from `data/` CSVs or JSON go in `web/lib/data/`.
- Use `loading.tsx` and `error.tsx` for route-level feedback.
- Keep bundle size small: dynamic-import heavy components, tree-shake unused deps.
